.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH antimony-package 1  "package " 
.SH NAME
antimony\-package \- Package a profile into a self\-contained executable
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBantimony package\fR [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-dest\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIPROFILE\fR> [\fIPASSTHROUGH\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Package a profile into a self\-contained executable
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dest\fR \fI<DEST>\fR
Where to export to. Defaults to current directory
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR \fI<VERSION>\fR
An optional version string for the package
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIPROFILE\fR>
The name of the profile/feature to export. If absent, export all user\-profiles/features
.TP
[\fIPASSTHROUGH\fR]
Run arguments
